Virtual machine is an emulation of a computer system, System virtual machines and Process virtual machines

Vagrant is an open-source software for building of Software Developement Enviroments like Virtualbox, it simplifies the virtualizations.

Vagrant was developed by Mitchell Hashimoto and John Bender

Ubuntu is an operating system for cloud computing, is free and open-source, was released in 2004.

Ubuntu is related to a humanist philosophy and theology coming from south africa

Command uname shows the kernel of the system

Zero-day means the day when a crucial lack of security is discovered by hackers
 